I've been working on a similar tool for a while - connet (
https://github.com/connet-dev/connet
). It builds upon QUIC (instead of wireguard), but I think from an enduser perspective the results ends up looking pretty similar.

comments.top:
Multi-tenant bugs slipping through tests is the scariest part of shipping fast with AI codegen. We've been working on Autonoma (
https://www.getautonoma.com/
) for exactly this, AI agents that do E2E testing by navigating your app like a real user and catching the stuff unit tests miss.
